# Bridge Platform — Module-by-Module Deep Dive

The Bridge Platform is an accessible messaging application built as a **microservices architecture**. It translates between speech, text, and sign language in real-time, tailoring the UI to four user profiles: **General**, **Deaf**, **Blind**, and **Mute**.

```mermaid
graph LR
    FE["5. Frontend Layer<br/>(React + Vite)"]
    GW["3. Gateway API<br/>(FastAPI :8000)"]
    STT["1. STT API<br/>(Vosk :8002)"]
    SLR["2. SLR API<br/>(TensorFlow :8003)"]
    TTS["4a. TTS API<br/>(gTTS :8001)"]
    AVA["4b. Sign Avatar API<br/>(Puppeteer :5003)"]

    FE -->|REST + WS| GW
    GW -->|proxy| STT
    GW -->|proxy| SLR
    GW -->|proxy| TTS
    GW -->|proxy| AVA
    FE -.->|direct call| TTS
    FE -.->|direct call| AVA
```

---

## Layer 1 — Input Layer: Speech-to-Text (STT) API

| | |
|---|---|
| **Port** | `8002` |
| **Framework** | FastAPI (Python) |
| **Engine** | [Vosk](https://alphacephei.com/vosk/) offline speech recognition |
| **Files** | [stt_main.py](file:///d:/bridgeapp/1_input_layer/stt_api/stt_main.py), [audio_processor.py](file:///d:/bridgeapp/1_input_layer/stt_api/audio_processor.py) |

### Core Functionality

This module converts **audio recordings → text**. It is the entry point for voice-input users.

**Request flow:**

1. **Receive audio** — endpoint `POST /speech-to-text` accepts any audio file (WAV, MP3, OGG, etc.) via multipart upload, along with optional `language`, `sample_rate`, and `noise_reduction` params.
2. **Convert to WAV** — `audio_processor.convert_to_wav()` shells out to **FFmpeg** to transcode the upload to 16 kHz mono WAV, the exact format Vosk expects. This bypasses Python's `audioop` module that was removed in Python 3.13.
3. **Transcribe** — Opens the WAV with the `wave` module, verifies it's mono PCM, then feeds 4000-frame chunks to a `KaldiRecognizer`. Partial results accumulate; a final `FinalResult()` call flushes remaining audio.
4. **Return** — JSON response with `transcribed_text`, `confidence`, and `language`.

**Authentication:** Bearer token validated in-line (`bridge-dev-token-123`).

**Model:** Uses a pre-downloaded Vosk model stored in the `model/` directory (loaded once at startup into `vosk_model`).

---

## Layer 2 — AI Processing Layer: Sign Language Recognition (SLR) API

| | |
|---|---|
| **Port** | `8003` |
| **Framework** | FastAPI (Python) |
| **Engine** | TensorFlow/Keras CNN ([isl_model.h5](file:///d:/bridgeapp/isl_model.h5)) |
| **Files** | [slr_main.py](file:///d:/bridgeapp/2_ai_processing_layer/sign_recognition_api/slr_main.py), [video_processor.py](file:///d:/bridgeapp/2_ai_processing_layer/sign_recognition_api/video_processor.py) |

### Core Functionality

This module converts **sign language video → text** by classifying individual frames against a 23-class ISL (Indian Sign Language) static alphabet model.

**Request flow:**

1. **Receive video** — endpoint `POST /video-to-text` accepts a video file upload.
2. **Extract frames** — `video_processor.extract_and_preprocess_frames()` uses **OpenCV** to:
   - Read frames, sampling every 5th frame (`skip_frames=5`) to reduce redundancy.
   - Convert BGR → RGB.
   - Resize each frame to **128×128** pixels (the model's expected input).
   - Normalize pixel values to `[0, 1]` range.
   - Return as a NumPy array of shape [(N, 128, 128, 3)](file:///d:/bridgeapp/5_frontend_layer/src/App.jsx#6-18).
3. **Predict** — Batch-predict all frames through the Keras CNN. If TensorFlow isn't available, a **mock engine** returns hardcoded letters for integration testing.
4. **Map predictions** — [map_predictions_to_letters()](file:///d:/bridgeapp/2_ai_processing_layer/sign_recognition_api/video_processor.py#43-71) takes the softmax output, picks the argmax for each frame, and maps the index to an ISL letter via a 23-label lookup: `A B C D E F G H I K L M N O P Q R S T U V W Y` (skipping J, X, Z — motion-based signs).
5. **Smooth** — [smooth_predictions()](file:///d:/bridgeapp/2_ai_processing_layer/sign_recognition_api/video_processor.py#72-86) uses **majority voting** (`Counter.most_common(1)`) across all detected letters to return a single dominant character.
6. **Return** — JSON with `transcribed_text` (one letter), `confidence`, `language`.

> [!NOTE]
> A separate, more advanced inference pipeline runs at **port 8006** (`D:\final_sign_to_txt\inference_simple`) for word/phrase-level recognition using MediaPipe keypoint extraction + LSTM. The frontend calls this directly via `bridgeApi.signVideoToTranscript()`.

---

## Layer 3 — Communication Kernel: Gateway API

| | |
|---|---|
| **Port** | `8000` |
| **Framework** | FastAPI (Python) |
| **Files** | [gateway_main.py](file:///d:/bridgeapp/3_communication_kernel/gateway_api/gateway_main.py), [config.py](file:///d:/bridgeapp/3_communication_kernel/gateway_api/config.py) |

### Core Functionality

The Gateway is the **central router and WebSocket hub**. It has two distinct roles:

#### A) REST Proxy (Microservice Router)

Four proxy endpoints forward requests from the frontend to the appropriate backend service using **httpx** async HTTP:

| Gateway Endpoint | Target Service | Config Key |
|---|---|---|
| `POST /api/speech-to-text` | STT API `:8002` | `STT_URL` |
| `POST /api/sign-to-text` | SLR API `:8003` | `SLR_URL` |
| `POST /api/text-to-speech` | TTS API `:8001` | `TTS_URL` |
| `POST /api/text-to-sign` | Avatar API `:5003` | `AVATAR_URL` |

Each proxy reads the upstream file/form data, re-sends it to the target microservice with the internal auth header, and pipes the JSON response back to the caller. All requests have a **180-second timeout**.

#### B) WebSocket Signaling (Real-Time Messaging)

The [ConnectionManager](file:///d:/bridgeapp/3_communication_kernel/gateway_api/gateway_main.py#18-36) class implements a **WhatsApp-style peer-to-peer message relay**:

- **Connect** — `WS /ws/{username}` accepts a WebSocket, stores it in `active_connections[username]`.
- **Message relay** — When a message arrives as `{"to": "recipient", "payload": "..."}`, the gateway tags it with `"from": sender_username` and forwards it to the recipient's WebSocket via [send_personal_message()](file:///d:/bridgeapp/3_communication_kernel/gateway_api/gateway_main.py#33-36).
- **Disconnect** — On `WebSocketDisconnect`, removes the connection from the map.

**CORS** is configured wide-open for local development (`allow_origins=["*"]`).

**Config** ([config.py](file:///d:/bridgeapp/3_communication_kernel/gateway_api/config.py)) — All microservice URLs and the shared auth token are configured via environment variables with localhost defaults.

---

## Layer 4a — Output Layer: Text-to-Speech (TTS) API

| | |
|---|---|
| **Port** | `8001` |
| **Framework** | FastAPI (Python) |
| **Engine** | Google TTS (`gTTS`) primary, [pyttsx3](file:///d:/bridgeapp/4_output_layer/tts_api/tts_main.py#65-73) fallback |
| **Files** | [tts_main.py](file:///d:/bridgeapp/4_output_layer/tts_api/tts_main.py), [text_processor.py](file:///d:/bridgeapp/4_output_layer/tts_api/text_processor.py) |

### Core Functionality

Converts **text → spoken audio MP3**. Primary output for Blind users.

**Request flow:**

1. **Receive request** — `POST /generate-speech` accepts a JSON body: `{text, language, voice, speed}`.
2. **Normalize text** — `text_processor.normalize_text()` cleans whitespace and expands common abbreviations (`Dr.` → `Doctor`, `e.g.` → `for example`, etc.) for natural-sounding speech.
3. **Generate audio (two-strategy fallback):**
   - **Strategy 1 (Online):** `gTTS` — Google's Text-to-Speech service. High quality, thread-safe. Generates an MP3 file.
   - **Strategy 2 (Offline fallback):** [pyttsx3](file:///d:/bridgeapp/4_output_layer/tts_api/tts_main.py#65-73) — Local SAPI5/espeak engine. Runs in a **separate `multiprocessing.Process`** with a 10-second timeout to avoid COM threading deadlocks in FastAPI's async workers.
4. **Serve audio** — The [audio/](file:///d:/bridgeapp/4_output_layer/tts_api/tts_main.py#50-58) directory is mounted as a static file directory. Returns `audio_url` pointing to `http://localhost:8001/audio/{uuid}.mp3`.

---

## Layer 4b — Output Layer: Sign Avatar API

| | |
|---|---|
| **Port** | `5003` |
| **Framework** | Express.js (Node.js) |
| **Engine** | Puppeteer (headless Chrome) + React 3D avatar build |
| **Files** | [server.js](file:///d:/bridgeapp/4_output_layer/sign_avatar_api/server.js) |

### Core Functionality

Converts **text → sign language avatar video (WebM)**. Primary output for Deaf users.

**Request flow:**

1. **Receive request** — `POST /generate-sign-video` accepts `{text: "..."}` JSON body.
2. **Launch headless browser** — Puppeteer opens a headless Chrome instance with GPU emulation (`swiftshader`), no sandbox, and autoplay enabled.
3. **Render the avatar** — Navigates to `http://localhost:5003/headless?text=...`, which serves a pre-built React application from the `build/` directory. This React app renders a 3D sign language avatar that performs the signs for each letter/word.
4. **Wait for completion** — Polls `window.renderComplete === true` (set by the React app when the avatar finishes signing).
5. **Extract video blob** — JavaScript within the headless page captures the rendering as a video blob (`window.capturedVideoBlob`), reads it via `FileReader` as a base64 data URL, and passes it back to Node.js.
6. **Save and serve** — Decodes the base64 data, writes it as `{uuid}.webm` to `public/videos/`, and returns the URL.

> [!IMPORTANT]
> This is a computationally heavy process — each request launches a full Chrome instance, renders 3D WebGL content, and records a video. The 300-second timeout reflects this.

---

## Layer 5 — Frontend Layer (React + Vite)

| | |
|---|---|
| **Port** | `5173` (Vite dev server) |
| **Framework** | React 18 + Vite |
| **Files** | [App.jsx](file:///d:/bridgeapp/5_frontend_layer/src/App.jsx), [Login.jsx](file:///d:/bridgeapp/5_frontend_layer/src/pages/Login.jsx), [ChatApp.jsx](file:///d:/bridgeapp/5_frontend_layer/src/pages/ChatApp.jsx), [ChatInput.jsx](file:///d:/bridgeapp/5_frontend_layer/src/components/ChatInput.jsx), [MessageList.jsx](file:///d:/bridgeapp/5_frontend_layer/src/components/MessageList.jsx), [bridgeApi.js](file:///d:/bridgeapp/5_frontend_layer/src/api/bridgeApi.js), [crypto.js](file:///d:/bridgeapp/5_frontend_layer/src/utils/crypto.js), [storage.js](file:///d:/bridgeapp/5_frontend_layer/src/utils/storage.js), [useUIReader.js](file:///d:/bridgeapp/5_frontend_layer/src/utils/useUIReader.js) |

### Core Functionality

The frontend is a **WhatsApp-style chat interface** with accessibility-adaptive features.

#### 5.1 Routing ([App.jsx](file:///d:/bridgeapp/5_frontend_layer/src/App.jsx))
- `/login` → Login page
- `/chat` → Chat interface
- `*` → Redirects to `/login`

#### 5.2 Login ([Login.jsx](file:///d:/bridgeapp/5_frontend_layer/src/pages/Login.jsx))
- User enters a **username** and selects a **profile** (General / Deaf / Blind / Mute).
- An AES encryption key is auto-derived from the username via [deriveKey()](file:///d:/bridgeapp/5_frontend_layer/src/utils/crypto.js#3-9) — `SHA-256(username_secure_salt_2024)`.
- Credentials stored in `sessionStorage` (ephemeral, cleared on tab close).

#### 5.3 Chat UI ([ChatApp.jsx](file:///d:/bridgeapp/5_frontend_layer/src/pages/ChatApp.jsx))
- **Contact sidebar** with an "Add Contact" button (adds by exact username).
- **WebSocket connection** — Connects to `ws://localhost:8000/ws/{username}` on mount. Incoming messages are decrypted and saved to IndexedDB.
- **Message sending** — Messages are AES-encrypted before being sent over the WebSocket as `{to, payload}`.
- **Bot simulation** — Messages to "Bridge AI Assistant" auto-reply after 1 second for testing.

#### 5.4 Chat Input ([ChatInput.jsx](file:///d:/bridgeapp/5_frontend_layer/src/components/ChatInput.jsx))
Supports **four input methods**:
1. **Text** — Standard keyboard input with Enter-to-send.
2. **Audio recording** — Uses `MediaRecorder` API to capture microphone audio; sends to STT API → transcribes → sends as text message.
3. **Video recording** — Records camera video for sign language; sends to the sign recognition API for transcription.
4. **Video upload** — Upload a pre-recorded sign language video file; sends to the inference pipeline at port 8006 ([signVideoToTranscript](file:///d:/bridgeapp/5_frontend_layer/src/api/bridgeApi.js#90-105)).

#### 5.5 Message Display ([MessageList.jsx](file:///d:/bridgeapp/5_frontend_layer/src/components/MessageList.jsx))
The [DynamicMessageBubble](file:///d:/bridgeapp/5_frontend_layer/src/components/MessageList.jsx#5-98) component **adapts per user profile**:

| Profile | Available translation actions on incoming messages |
|---|---|
| **General** | Plain text only |
| **Blind** | 🔊 "Audio" button → calls TTS API → attaches audio player |
| **Deaf** | 🤟 "Sign-Video" button → calls Avatar API → attaches video player |
| **Mute** | Both 🔊 Audio and 🤟 Sign-Video buttons |

Rendered media (audio/video) is embedded inline in the message bubble.

#### 5.6 Encryption ([crypto.js](file:///d:/bridgeapp/5_frontend_layer/src/utils/crypto.js))
- **Key derivation** — `SHA-256(secret)` via CryptoJS.
- **Encrypt** — `AES.encrypt(plaintext, key)`.
- **Decrypt** — `AES.decrypt(ciphertext, key)`. Returns `[Encrypted Message - Key Mismatch]` on failure.

#### 5.7 Storage ([storage.js](file:///d:/bridgeapp/5_frontend_layer/src/utils/storage.js))
- Uses **IndexedDB** (via `idb-keyval`) for persistent storage.
- All messages are **encrypted before saving** and **decrypted on read**.
- Contacts are stored alongside a default "Bridge AI Assistant" contact.

#### 5.8 Accessibility Reader ([useUIReader.js](file:///d:/bridgeapp/5_frontend_layer/src/utils/useUIReader.js))
- A React hook that provides a `speak()` function.
- **Only active for the Blind profile** — uses the browser's `SpeechSynthesis` API to read out UI events (e.g., "New message from Alice", "Selected conversation with Bob").

---

## Orchestration: [start_all.py](file:///d:/bridgeapp/start_all.py)

Launches **all 6 services** simultaneously using `subprocess.Popen`:

| Service | Port | Command |
|---|---|---|
| Sign Avatar Server | 5003 | `node server.js` |
| TTS API | 8001 | `uvicorn tts_main:app --port 8001` |
| STT API | 8002 | `uvicorn stt_main:app --port 8002` |
| SLR API | 8003 | `uvicorn slr_main:app --port 8003` |
| Gateway API | 8000 | `uvicorn gateway_main:app --port 8000` |
| React Frontend | 5173 | `npm run dev` |

Waits 10 seconds for boot, then enters an infinite loop. `Ctrl+C` terminates all processes.
